The '''Squib Reclamation Fleet''' was an arm of the [[Squib Merchandising Consortium]], the body that governed the [[Squib/Legends|Squibs]]. The fleet was composed primarily of tapered, Squib-designed [[needle ship]]s cobbled together from pieces of salvage. Each needle ship was crewed by 20 Squibs and held enough [[Foodstuff/Legends|consumables]] for three months. The [[Flagship/Legends|flagship]] at some point before the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]] was the ''[[Wholesale]]''; after the [[Battle of Yavin/Legends|Battle of Yavin]], it was the ''[[Thrifty]]''. This latter ship was the personal craft of King [[Ebareebaveebeedee]] and thus served as the Squib [[Momship]]. Squib Reclamation vessels were rarely equipped with weapons, instead relying on skilled [[Tractor beam/Legends|tractor beam]] operation for defense.

The Squib Reclamation Fleet was a major Squib employer, and its setup was not unlike a military fleet. In fact, Squibs could be considered AWOL if they failed to report for duty. During the [[Imperial Era/Legends|Imperial era]], Squib laborers stationed aboard Imperial [[Capital ship/Legends|capital ships]] supplied the fleet with information regarding trade opportunities and coordinates whenever the ship made a garbage dump. This made them important [[Spy/Legends|spies]] in the eyes of the fleet, although the Imperials viewed them as nothing more than [[Slavery/Legends|slaves]].

